Make brms model print list

Source: R/fn_make.R
make_brms_mdl_print_ls.Rd

make_brms_mdl_print_ls() is a Make function that creates a new R object. Specifically, this function implements an algorithm to make brms model print list. The function returns Brms model print (a list).

make_brms_mdl_print_ls(
  mdl_ls,
  label_stub_1L_chr,
  caption_1L_chr,
  output_type_1L_chr = "PDF",
  digits_1L_dbl = 2,
  big_mark_1L_chr = " "
)

Arguments

mdl_ls

Model (a list)
label_stub_1L_chr

Label stub (a character vector of length one)
caption_1L_chr

Caption (a character vector of length one)
output_type_1L_chr

Output type (a character vector of length one), Default: 'PDF'
digits_1L_dbl

Digits (a double vector of length one), Default: 2
big_mark_1L_chr

Big mark (a character vector of length one), Default: ' '

Value

Brms model print (a list)
